About the Business

Uncle Vic "Vito" came to America from Sicily in 1907. As a young man, Vito worked for his family's dairy business making cheeses while developing a love for great pizza. In honor of Uncle Vito & inspired by the great pizzerias of New York City, Uncle Vito's Slice of NY opened in Spring 2007.…

    Uncle Vito's is the place to go in Davis if you want a thinner, New York style slice of pizza. It's a lively restaurant that serves up very flavorful pizza pies, slices, and fries. Oh, and if you want a drink at the bar... they have that too!

    You'll find Uncle Vito's on the corner decked out with its own NY art - it's impossible to miss. The restaurant is on the smaller side, so if you have a big party, this might not be the ideal place to go. Uncle Vito's is split into two main sections: the bar and the restaurant with a patio available as well.

    The place can get quite loud as there are sports and sports fan who frequently come to watch the game. So basically, if you want to study or have a quiet night out... this isn't the place!

    This is the place, however, for some great pizza. I love the fact that you can order by the slice, and the slices are quite large. I had two slices tonight and I was totally full. Each slice is quite filling, they don't skimp!

    I wanted to try something traditional and something non, so I went for the pepperoni as my traditional choice and their special Mexican slice as my non-traditional. The pepperoni was good and serviceable... but the Mexican special slice was incredible. It had a great balance of flavors - a bit spicy with the sauce, some savory meats, and lettuce flavored with ranch to cool things off. Amazing! I'd go back in hopes that this pizza is still featured. Definitely different, but definitely delicious.

    I also had the chance to share a garlic fry with my friend. If you like crispy thin fries doused in fresh garlic and parm... this is a MUST HAVE. The portion was very big, and we wolfed the whole thing down. It makes me want to try their Thai fries next as I hear they are very popular.

    I only have a few qualms with Uncle Vito's. One, the noise level can get quite loud and distracting. You have to pick the right time to go if you don't want to have sports fans screaming and clapping all around you. And two, while the food is very tasty, it does leave you feeling a bit greasy in the end. The heaviness of it all can weigh you down.

    But overall, I'd definitely recommend Uncle Vitos. I'm excited to make my next trip out there very soon.

    I visited Uncle Vito's Slice of NY with my uncle and my boyfriend after a day of swimming. We shared a large Sicilian pizza and the Big Apple Spinach salad. The Sicilian was pretty good; the tomato sauce is indeed a bit spicy. The crust is /perfect/: thin where it should be thin (under the sauce and cheese and toppings) and thick where it should be thick (crusty edges). The Big Apple Spinach salad was also pretty good. As my uncle said, "With bacon on top, how can it be bad?" Although, a bit over dressed.

    If I were to return on my own, I'd order a classic NY Cheese and I think it would probably be perfect. My theory is this: when pizza is done right, it doesn't need those extra toppings. In fact, the extra toppings muddy the purity of a well made pizza. See you soon, Uncle Vito!

    I have many memories of this place with the late night drinking and cravings for pizza. Such a great deal to be able to get a pint and a slice for 5 dollars. There are plenty of TVS for all your viewing pleasure whether it be sports or some drama on. You will not be able to enjoy hearing what is said, but at least there is subtitles.

    Why did it take me so long to try this place? I've been living in Davis for over three years and always passed up this place. I went on a Monday evening to watch the Warriors game and was glad. They have plenty of tv's and lots of seating and an outside seating area. So this is the perfect place if you're looking to catch a game.  

    We made it in time for happy hour and got two tangerine wheat beers and two cocktails. My bf and I also shared an order of Thai fries and a slice of tomato pesto pizza. This came out to $20. Perfect for the college budget.

    If you've never been and didn't read up on some reviews, it could be a little confusing when you walk in and try to order. Order at the bar, you'll get a number and then pick up near the big window next to the condiments.

    Food was solid and inexpensive. The food came out fast and quick and it was delicious. Pizza is pizza to me. It doesn't take much for me to be impressed by pizza but the tomato pesto was amazing. Super yummy and you get a large slice for $4. You can definitely split a slice and fries with another person. The Thai fries were awesome as well. I still prefer teabos but these were good.

    Service was okay... The bartender could have been a little more welcoming. But it looked like she was the only one so I guess she was busy? All in all, I would definitely come back here to eat with friends or to watch a game. Great spot in Davis.

    Tomato pesto

    Thai fries

    ALL YOU CAN EAT SLICES FROM 11:30AM-1PM ON THE WEEKDAYS?! I think you're calling my name!

    Came here for the first time because I was craving some pizza, and my friend and I wanted to try a different joint. We were surprised that there was an all you can eat option for such a low cost! Your all you can eat pizza also comes with a refillable fountain drink. Ugh, music to a struggling college student's ears,

    I was pleasantly surprised by the size of the slice. They're all fairly large and there's always an abundance of toppings on your slice, so you definitely get the bang for you buck here at Uncle Vito's.

    Very bar-like ambiance and can get busy during those pesky game nights. Lol.

    I've come back to Vito's on several occasions after that first surprise. Now, you've got to have a go at the Thai fries, because they're AMAZING. The fries are the perfect cut and fried to perfection. All of the sauces and herbs really make it what it is. Warning: a bit spicy for those of you who can't handle the heat.

    I wish I could come here more often!

    I really really really like this place. It's probably the best place in Yolo County to grab a beer and a bite to eat while also watching the latest sporting event. Davis is a short drive for me and my mother , who uses a jazzy power chair. We usually use the Yolobus to do the transporting and Vito's has since become our go-to destination on Sundays.
    Vito's has many beers on tap and the cocktails they serve here can really work up an appetite. My mother and I started off with the Thai fries. It was the most popular Yelp recommendation and it delivers. It's a order of fries with an Asian twist, really good beer food for sure.
    The pizza is what they're know for and once it arrives at the table one can see why. The pizza by the slice is bigger than the plate they serve it on. The toppings are fresh and tasty but the crust could be crisper as each slice goes limp after picking it up. That didn't stop me nor my mother as we both finished ours.
    People of all ages enjoy this place. Go check it out and see why.
